[ti:The Death of a Ghost]
[00:00.35]Lesson 30|第30课
[00:02.09]The death of a ghost|一个“幽灵”的死亡
[00:09.46]Why did the two brothers keep the secret?|为什么这两兄弟要保守这个秘密呢？
[00:13.75]For years, villagers believed that Endley farm was haunted.|多年来，村民们一直相信恩德利农场有鬼魂出没。
[00:18.87]The farm was owned by two brothers, Joe and Bob Cox.|这个农场由两兄弟共同拥有，他们分别是乔（Joe Cox）和鲍勃（Bob Cox）。
[00:23.74]They employed a few farmhands, but no one was willing to work there long.|他们雇了一些农场工人，但没有人愿意在那里长期工作。
[00:29.26]Every time a worker gave up his job, he told the same story.|每次有工人辞职时，他都会讲述同一个故事。
[00:34.95]Farm labourers said that they always woke up to find that work had been done overnight.|农场工人表示，他们每天醒来后都会发现：前一晚的工作已经全部完成了。
[00:41.59]Hay had been cut and cowsheds had been cleaned.|干草已经被割下，牛棚也已经被清理干净了。
[00:46.03]A farm worker, who stayed up all night, claimed to have seen a figure cutting corn in the moonlight.|一位整夜未眠的农场工人声称，他在月光下看到有人正在收割玉米。
[00:53.64]In time, it became an accepted fact that the Cox brothers employed a conscientious ghost that did most of their work for them.|随着时间的推移，人们逐渐接受了这样一个事实：Cox兄弟雇佣了一个“尽职尽责”的幽灵，这个幽灵为他们完成了大部分工作。
[01:04.02]No one suspected that there might be someone else on the farm who had never been seen.|没有人怀疑农场里可能还有另一个从未被任何人发现过的人。
[01:10.07]This was indeed the case.|事实确实如此。
[01:12.81]A short time ago, villagers were astonished to learn that the ghost of Endley had died.|不久前，村民们惊讶地得知：恩德利的鬼魂终于“去世”了。
[01:20.00]Everyone went to the funeral, for the 'ghost' was none other than Eric Cox,|大家都参加了葬礼，因为那个“鬼魂”其实就是埃里克·考克斯。
[01:26.85]a third brother who was supposed to have died as a young man.|第三个兄弟本应在年轻时就去世的。
[01:31.43]After the funeral, Joe and Bob revealed a secret which they had kept for over fifty years.|葬礼结束后，乔和鲍勃透露了一个他们保守了五十多年的秘密。
[01:39.48]Eric had been the eldest son of the family, very much older than his two brothers.|埃里克是家里的长子，比他的两个弟弟年纪大很多。
[01:45.49]He had been obliged to join the army during the Second World War.|在第二次世界大战期间，他被迫加入了军队。
[01:50.25]As he hated army life, he decided to desert his regiment.|由于他极其厌恶军队生活，他决定逃离自己的部队。
[01:56.13]When he learnt that he would be sent abroad,|当他得知自己将被派往国外时，
[01:58.99]he returned to the farm and his father hid him until the end of the war.|他回到了农场，他的父亲把他藏了起来，直到战争结束。
[02:04.41]Fearing the authorities, Eric remained in hiding after the war as well.|由于害怕当局的追捕，埃里克在战争结束后仍然选择隐藏起来，没有公开露面。
[02:10.36]His father told everybody that Eric had been killed in action.|他的父亲告诉所有人，埃里克在战斗中牺牲了。
[02:15.03]The only other people who knew the secret were Joe and Bob.|唯一知道这个秘密的人还有乔和鲍勃。
[02:19.49]They did not even tell their wives.|他们甚至都没有告诉自己的妻子。
[02:22.69]When their father died they thought it their duty to keep Eric in hiding.|当他们的父亲去世后，他们认为有责任继续隐藏埃里克（Eric）的身份。
[02:27.70]All these years, Eric had lived as a recluse.|这些年来，埃里克一直过着隐居的生活。
[02:32.66]He used to sleep during the day and work at night,|他过去常常在白天睡觉，晚上工作。
[02:35.66]quite unaware of the fact that he had become the ghost of Endley.|他完全不知道自己已经变成了“恩德利”的幽灵（即：他已经变成了一个没有实体、只能以某种无形方式存在的人或存在）。
[02:40.60]When he died, however, his brothers found it impossible to keep the secret any longer.|然而，当他去世后，他的兄弟们发现再也无法保守这个秘密了。
